From: Limeng <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
Date: Mon, 29 Feb 2016 13:46:01 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1592/1594] driver: video: mxsfb: fix a bug of lcdif

axi clock should not be disabled at the end of mxsfb_pan_display().
Because it will result in lcdif controller works abnormally if disable
axi clock.

Signed-off-by: Meng Li <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/video/fbdev/mxsfb.c |    2 --
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/fbdev/mxsfb.c b/drivers/video/fbdev/mxsfb.c
index 9d84e07..328e5cd 100644
--- a/drivers/video/fbdev/mxsfb.c
+++ b/drivers/video/fbdev/mxsfb.c
@@ -922,8 +922,6 @@ static int mxsfb_pan_display(struct fb_var_screeninfo *var,
 	writel(CTRL1_CUR_FRAME_DONE_IRQ_EN,
 		host->base + LCDC_CTRL1 + REG_SET);
 
-	mxsfb_disable_axi_clk(host);
-
 	return 0;
 }
 
